  "title": "Utah Just Banned July 4th Fireworks Statewide",
  "script": "No fireworks. Not one! Utah Governor Spencer Cox just declared a state of emergency and banned all personal fireworks statewide through July 5. That's the entire Fourth of July. Right now, 94% of Utah is in severe or extreme drought. This fire season: 354 fires, more than 141,000 acres burned. Cox says personal fireworks — backyard sparklers included — are banned everywhere in the state. Some permitted public shows are still happening. But if you were planning to light anything yourself in Utah this week, that's over. The timing: America turns 250 on July 4th. The single most fireworks-saturated holiday in American history — and Utah's sitting it out. Cox is essentially saying: the birthday party is on. Just without the part where things explode. Is 250 years of tradition worth a valley full of smoke?",
